note._content:
Most likely maiz in arpilleras (Hessian (pron.: /ˈhɛsi.ən/), or burlap in the US and Canada,[1] is a woven fabric usually made from skin of the jute plant).
Maize (pron.: /ˈmeɪz/ mayz; Zea mays subsp. mays L, from Spanish: maíz after Taíno mahiz), known in some English-speaking countries as corn (meaning grain)
